{
    "en": {
        "SS_EXPANSIONDEF_NAME": "Sandswept",
        "SS_EXPANSIONDEF_DESC": "Adds content from the 'Sandswept' expansion to the game <3. Have fun <3.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_AMBER_KNIFE_NAME": "Amber Knife",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_AMBER_KNIFE_PICKUP": "Chance to fire a piercing knife that grants barrier on hit.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_AMBER_KNIFE_DESCRIPTION": "Gain a {chance}% chance on hit to fire a <style=cIsDamage>piercing knife</style> for {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) base damage that grants {percentBarrierGain}% plus an additional {flatBarrierGain} <style=cIsHealing>barrier</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_AMBER_KNIFE_LORE": "Order: Amber Knife\nTracking Number: 534*****\nEstimated Delivery: 06/15/2056\nShipping Method: High Priority\nShipping Address: Outer Ring Lab, Venus\nShipping Details:\n\nThis is an ancient ritual artifact, once used by Neptunian priests in sacrifices, said to protect them from attack and assassination. This was not without credence, it seems, as the knife operates similarly to the ultra-phasic shield technology used in the assassination of Mars's ambassador two months back.\n\nOf course, we can't use such an old and fragile weapon in our own operations, but its effect seems more potent than what the assassin used. Along with serving your planet, you'll receive generous funding to discover how it works and incorporate it into something more usable.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FRACTURED_TIMEPIECE_NAME": "Fractured Timepiece",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FRACTURED_TIMEPIECE_PICKUP": "Using your Utility skill heals you and reduces Special skill cooldown.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FRACTURED_TIMEPIECE_DESCRIPTION": "On using your <style=cIsUtility>Utility skill</style>, heal for {basePercentHealing}% (+{stackPercentHealing}% per stack) of your <style=cIsHealing>maximum health</style> and reduce your <style=cIsUtility>Special skill cooldown</style> by {specialCooldownReduction}%.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FRACTURED_TIMEPIECE_LORE": "Order: Timepiece\nTracking Number: 864*******\nEstimated Delivery: 02/23/2054\nShipping Method: Priority\nShipping Address: Hall of Reverence, Mars\nShipping Details:\n\nOur team found this in the desert, where the ancient Hall once stood, before it burned. I think someone wanted very badly to protect it from the Purge, as it was carefully packed where we found it. You can likely extract more knowledge from it than we can, and it originally belonged to the Hall.\n\nThere was also a note from the Time Keeper of that era, which I have attached to the shipment. No one here can read the ancient language, so I hope you can decipher it.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_RED_SPRING_WATER_NAME": "Red Spring Water",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_RED_SPRING_WATER_PICKUP": "Increases health regeneration for each unique buff you have.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_RED_SPRING_WATER_DESCRIPTION": "Increases <style=cIsHealing>health regeneration</style> by {baseRegen} HP/s, plus {baseRegenPerBuff} HP/s (+{stackRegenPerBuff} HP/s per stack) for <style=cIsUtility>each unique buff you have</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_RED_SPRING_WATER_LORE": "<style=cMono>\n//--AUTO-transcription FROM UES [REDACTED] --//\n</style>\n«I don't know if you should drink that.»\n\n«Why not? I feel incredible!»\n\n«We don't know what's in that liquid. No xenobiologist would recommend drinking an unknown red liquid from an even more unknown planet.»\n\n«Well, it only helped me. Down there we can get everything we need.»\n\n«Better to go without than poison yourself. When we gave it to Kyle to help him heal, it only made things worse.»\n\n«Well, unlike Kyle, I'm not sick. Maybe it's because of this stuff that my wounds are healing much faster.»\n\n«That's your funeral.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_NAME": "Temporal Transistor",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_PICKUP": "Chance on kill to store an extra jump.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_DESCRIPTION": "Gain a {chance}% chance on kill to store an <style=cIsUtility>extra jump</style>. Can store up to {baseMaxJumps} (+{stackMaxJumps} per stack) <style=cIsUtility>extra jumps</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_LORE": "<style=cMono>//--AUTO-transcription FROM UES CARGO HOLD 3 [REDACTED] --//</style>\n\n«I've got a strange shipment here. Come see, I know you like this stuff.»\n\n«One second, I need to finish packing. Just describe it to me.»\n\n«Well, when I picked it up, I had a strange feeling. The cargo hold seemed different, but I didn't think much of it until I looked at my own limbs. It took me a second to realize I was looking through my body, like, from five years ago. Crazy. I dropped it and everything went back to normal.»\n\n«Surreal. I'll have to test it when I'm done. Do you know what it is?»\n\n«The entry log only says 'transistor'. I suppose I can see it, given the shape and all, but it's huge. Makes sense, considering what it does. I wonder what they'll use it for.»\n\n«What do you mean 'transistor'?»\n\n«Oh. You know, those things that make computers work.»\n\n«Well, my sister works with tech, but that's a bit vague.»\n\n«What?»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_RADAR_NAME": "Pocket Radar",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_RADAR_PICKUP": "Camouflaged chests are easier to see and appear more often.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_RADAR_DESCRIPTION": "Camouflaged chests are easier to see and are guaranteed to spawn 1 (+1 per stack) extra time per stage.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_RADAR_LORE": "",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_POCKET_RADAR_NAME": "Dark Flash",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_POCKET_RADAR_DESCRIPTION": "Open a Camouflaged Chest.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SILVER_CORD_NAME": "Silver Cord",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SILVER_CORD_PICKUP": "Gain a shock drone. Drone attacks have a chance to shock nearby enemies.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SILVER_CORD_DESCRIPTION": "Gain a <style=cIsUtility>Shock Drone</style>. Your drones have a {chance}% chance to <style=cIsUtility>shock</style> up to {baseMaxTargets} (+{stackMaxTargets} per stack) targets dealing {damage}% <style=cIsDamage>TOTAL DAMAGE</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SILVER_CORD_LORE": "Transcript of a call from the CEO of the UES yelling at HDTF Inc. about the loss of 10,000 units of each drone.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DISSONANT_VEIL_NAME": "Dissonant Veil",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DISSONANT_VEIL_PICKUP": "Become invisible when using your Equipment. Going invisible instantly drops combat and danger. Recharges over time.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DISSONANT_VEIL_DESCRIPTION": "On using your Equipment, become <style=cIsUtility>invisible</style> for {cloakBuffDuration}s. While <style=cIsUtility>invisible</style>, drop combat and danger. Recharges every {baseRechargeTime} seconds (-{stackRechargeTime}% per stack).",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DISSONANT_VEIL_LORE": "Transcript of dialogue between the captain of the UES Contact Light and a divine figure about a stolen construct.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BLEEDING_WITNESS_NAME": "Bleeding Witness",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BLEEDING_WITNESS_PICKUP": "Your damage-over-time effects heal all allies.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BLEEDING_WITNESS_DESCRIPTION": "{hemorrhageChance}% chance on hit to inflict <style=cIsDamage>hemorrhage</style> for {hemorrhageDamage}% base damage. Your <style=cIsDamage>damage-over-time effects</style> <style=cIsHealing>heal</style> all allies for {baseDoTHealing}% (+{stackDoTHealing}% per stack) of their <style=cIsHealing>maximum health</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BLEEDING_WITNESS_LORE": "> Automated report 3947b729237d17//?v=7YXoXter6H0 now available from batch record 62a73bd8473f8914239c9a837f.\n> Please consult record 62a73bd8473f8914239c9a837f for additional details during your review.\n> Report type: machine transcription > language profile base 'HotR'\n> Source: 62a73bd8473f8914239c9a837f (Unknown Material Artifact no.3715)\n> Priority: High\n> Report Contents:\n\n-- beginning of marked excerpt for review --\n\n[your excellence]. The scout has returned from the [white plane].\n\nWHERE IS THE SCOUT?\n\nThese are its remains, [your excellence].\n\nWHAT COULD HAVE DONE THIS? THIS IS A PLANET INHABITED BY INFERIOR CREATURES.\n\nThe scout was sent back through the [interstice], by some unknown creature, as if it were a message to us. Of the rest of the group, no trace.\n\nTHE ARTIFACT'S CREATOR, WITHOUT A DOUBT. A POWERFUL GUARDIAN. THEY ARE STILL THERE...\n\nSo it seems, [your excellence]. Whatever is in the [white plane], poses an enormous danger to us. Perhaps it is best to leave it alone.\n\nIF ITS CREATOR IS THERE, THEN THE ARTIFACT MUST ALSO BE THERE. YOUR COWARDICE CHANGES NOTHING; WE MUST RECOVER IT. HAIL THE [red plane].\n\n...so be it, [your excellence]. Hail the [red plane].\n\n-- End of record --\n\n-- End of marked excerpt for review --\n\n> TRANSLATION ERRORS: 4\n> 1> [your excellence] could not be fully translated.\n> 2> [interstice] could not be fully translated.\n> 3> [white plane] could not be fully translated.\n> 4> [red plane] could not be fully translated.\n\n> Please consult report b438ff73774c9801238d48130d048cd757a for the full audio.\n===================================================",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CEREMONIAL_JAR_NAME": "Ceremonial Jar",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CEREMONIAL_JAR_PICKUP": "Enemies hit by any skill are linked. Linked enemies take massive damage.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CEREMONIAL_JAR_DESCRIPTION": "Enemies hit by any <style=cIsUtility>skill</style> are <style=cIsDamage>linked</style>, up to {linkedEnemiesRequirement} times. Linked enemies take {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>base damage</style> and cannot be <style=cIsDamage>linked</style> for {linkedEnemyCooldown} seconds.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CEREMONIAL_JAR_LORE": "«In the early days, the resin was found only in a few small towns and villages of the dune people. This slow start was but a quiet harbinger of its takeover, which culminated in the crusades of those now called the 'stained generation', for whom the resin had been present since birth.\n\nAs the resin's cultural importance grew in those isolated places, it ceased to be an equal symbiosis and became a superior deity. It was worshipped as a god, whose existence was unquestionable and whose gifts were powerful, and the stained generation waged a crusade across all of Afelia to spread it.\n\nAt first, the crusades met only skepticism and rejection from those unaccustomed to the resin's presence. Some doubted its existence; others doubted its power; and those who doubted nothing, sensibly feared its influence. Unable to demonstrate the resin's existence or power without returning to their home cities, the crusaders recruited only a few. But with these new allies, they found a way to transport the resin, and so its first vessel was created.\n\nDespite the simplicity of its design, this original clay urn became the cornerstone of the resin's propagation. The original urn was worshipped as an idol. The dune people gave it what they had, allowing the resin to grow. Moved from city to city, from village to village, the urn dispelled all doubts about the resin's power or existence, quickly integrating itself into the dune people's warrior civilization. Those who continued to warn about the resin's influence were bribed by its power, and those who could not be bribed were fed to the new god of Afelia.»\n\n- Tragedy of Afelia",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_GLACIAL_PLASMA_NAME": "Glacial Plasma",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_GLACIAL_PLASMA_PICKUP": "Activating your primary skill also conjures a freezing lance. Chance to freeze stunned enemies on hit.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_GLACIAL_PLASMA_DESCRIPTION": "Activating your <style=cIsUtility>primary skill</style> also conjures a <style=cIsDamage>piercing lance</style> dealing {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) damage and <style=cIsUtility>freezes</style> enemies. Recharges in 10 seconds. Your <style=cIsUtility>stuns</style> have a {stunToFreezeChance}% chance to <style=cIsUtility>freeze</style> for {stunToFreezeDuration} seconds.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_GLACIAL_PLASMA_LORE": "UES [REDACTED] transcription about a shipment of frozen alien equipment.\n\n«Drink.»\n\n«This is... something. I've never seen anything like it... it's an unprecedented discovery.»\n\n«I'd like to think so. The potential of an object like this is practically limitless, not just in engineering—it's capable of so much more. Temperatures previously only accessible in isolated labs are now applicable anywhere, with just a touch of this thing.»\n\n«How did you discover this? And how did you synthesize something so strange so quickly?»\n\n«Well, um...»\n\n«Um? Oh, no, I know that look on your face. What did you do?»\n\n«Well, remember that High Court ambassador?»\n\n«You couldn't have done that.»\n\n«Maybe I did.»\n\n«We're screwed, you know. We at [REDACTED] are dead. You don't mess with the High Court, plain and simple. You know that.»\n\n«Allow me to disagree. I've had it for over a month...»\n\n«WHAT?»\n\n«...for over a month, and no one has come to check. I think it's time to pass this sample on to someone else. Let them deal with the consequences, and we'll come out unscathed with a good sum.»\n\n«And we'll just lie about its origin? What happens when the High Court knocks on their door? Even if the Court doesn't kill us, our buyer will.»\n\n«We don't need to lie. Have you seen what this thing is capable of? To the UES or any of its potential competitors, it's too valuable to pass up.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TORN_FEATHER_NAME": "Torn Feather",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TORN_FEATHER_PICKUP": "Press {FEATHERKEY} to dash in any direction. Recharges on touching the ground.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TORN_FEATHER_DESCRIPTION": "Press {FEATHERKEY} to <style=cIsUtility>dash in any direction</style>, up to 2 times before touching the ground. Gain {baseMovementSpeedGain}% (+{stackMovementSpeedGain}% per stack) <style=cIsUtility>movement speed</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TORN_FEATHER_LORE": "<style=cMono>\n//--AUTO-transcription FROM UES CARGO HOLD 6 [REDACTED] --//\n</style>\n«Wow...»\n\n«Pretty weird, huh?»\n\n«Yeah, it's like... holding a dream in your hands.»\n\n«I know that feeling. Every now and then, these damn steel pipes seem blessed by someone or something, hard to resist the temptation to grab it and fly.»\n\n«... uh-huh.»\n\n«But...»\n\n«Hey!»\n\n«...we must not give in. The UESC's steel boot is fast and painful.»\n\n«...yeah, you're right.»\n\n«Right! Like many things, you'll learn. But I don't blame you. Honestly, this is probably the most magical thing I've ever seen in these docks. It deserved a place in the Hall of Reverence, but I guess some lucky person got to it first. Time will tell when the Martians get their divine hands on it. They always get everything, in the end.»\n\n...\n\n«Well, now you're just staring at it.»\n\n«Ah, right! See, even I, with my experience, am not completely immune to these things. Well; into the abyss of the cargo container!»\n\n«...you'll get used to it, in time. Just try not to think about it, especially while it's still in this dock. For us, let's get back to work.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_NAME": "Hallowed Ichor",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_PICKUP": "Chests can be reopened once more... <color=#FF7F7F>BUT reopening them permanently increases difficulty.</color>",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_DESCRIPTION": "Chests can be <style=cIsUtility>reopened {baseExtraChestInteractions} (+{stackExtraChestInteractions} per stack) times</style>, but <style=cIsUtility>reopening</style> them permanently increases <style=cIsUtility>difficulty</style> by 30%. <style=cDeath>Difficulty increase scales with chest rarity</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_LORE": "This shall be the most powerful creation I will grant you. I have created many of these artifacts for parasites like you, but this one cost me far more. It will be given only to a few of my most loyal servants. With proper use, it will recoup the resources spent on its creation.\n\nThis is my blood, sealed in a vessel of my design. Blood of a superior being. It grants me—along with my traitorous brother—the power to shape compositions. One transfusion is enough to manifest this effect. In such a small quantity, of course, it does not grant all of my powers, but it will allow you to create more of those trinkets you grow so attached to.\n\nHowever, its use will not go unnoticed. He will feel your presence and send his parasites to hunt you. If you use your power to craft proper weapons and avoid facing him head-on, I don't think you'll have trouble destroying the pursuers.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_NAME": "Sequenced Fate",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_PICKUP": "Shrine of Order appears more often and grants additional random items.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_DESCRIPTION": "Using a <style=cIsUtility>Shrine of Order</style> grants {baseExtraItemsCount} (+{stackExtraItemsCount} per stack) <style=cIsUtility>additional random items</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Shrine of Order appears more often</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_LORE": "What is this? Some kind of interface?\n\nI see. It is not one of my constructs, but competent. Though not required, you created something of your own again. Well done. You learn quickly.\n\nWhat you propose... is interesting. Such a construct would create perfect order, as you say, but there is no need for this ivory stone. There is nothing to organize beyond my own trinkets. As you noted, the effects are only useful with greater variety. Still, you may invest in just one copy here, as a test, if you wish.\n\nBut what is most curious is the structure; you know the methods of my constructs, for you have worked with them—but this is organized differently. The ability to design proves that you are not so stupid as to create a disobedience shaped by my teachings and hand it to me. Explain the reason for your deviation.\n\nFascinating. Because of my hatred for them, I never even considered using this planet's parasites for my own ends. I suppose you are proof of their competence. I like the idea; it would be absolute revenge. This shrine is a simple thing, but I... WE... could create much greater gifts for them. Bind them to my will and set them against him. Creating more copies will be trivial. It is only a stone, after all, but within it lie the seeds of this plan, and my brother's favorite pets will plant them.\n\nYou have already proven yourself a viable investment. I invite you to fully oversee the next construction—with the dye you proved your ability to create, and with this, your ability to design.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_THEIR_PROMINENCE_NAME": "Their Prominence",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_THEIR_PROMINENCE_PICKUP": "Using a Shrine has a chance to activate the Mountain challenge. <color=#FF7F7F>Teleporters periodically summon Lunar Fissures.</color>",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_THEIR_PROMINENCE_DESCRIPTION": "Using a Shrine has a {baseChance}% (+{stackChance}% per stack) chance to activate the <style=cIsUtility>Mountain challenge</style>. Teleporters summon {baseLunarFissureCount} (+{stackLunarFissureCount} per Mountain challenge) <style=cDeath>lunar fissures</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_THEIR_PROMINENCE_LORE": "«Two brothers, at the edge of the well. <style=cIsVoid>Both young, both innocent.</style>»\n«A worm falls in. A new world found. <style=cDeath>One betrays.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One repents.</style>»\n«Two brothers, working in the workshop. <style=cIsVoid>Both respectful, both powerful.</style>»\n«[Compositions] discovered. Guardians created. <style=cIsVoid>Both in awe, both proud.</style>»\n«Two brothers, seeking a way out. <style=cIsVoid>Both hopeful. Both curious.</style>»\n«Society found. <style=cDeath>One sympathizes.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One grows irritated.</style>»\n«Two brothers, ethically divided. <style=cDeath>One a tyrant.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One indulgent.</style>»\n«Teleporter created. Choice made. <style=cDeath>One regrets.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One is betrayed.</style>»\n«Two brothers, separated by space. <style=cDeath>One enslaves.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One frees.</style>»\n«A glow appears in the sky. <style=cDeath>One enraged.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One hopeful.</style>»\n«Two brothers. Their times draw near. <style=cDeath>One a king.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One an exile.</style>»\n«God overthrown. Anarchy established. <style=cDeath>One vanished.</style> <style=cIsUtility>One forgotten.</style>»\n«Two brothers. <style=cIsVoid>Never... to meet again.</style>»\n\n---------------------\n> Translated from the Lemurian scribe language, found in the Temple of the Ancients by the UES team. Burn if desired.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FESTERING_HUNGER_NAME": "Festering Hunger",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FESTERING_HUNGER_PICKUP": "Chance to inflict decrepify on enemies on hit. Moving near decrepit enemies increases movement speed. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Smoldering Documents</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FESTERING_HUNGER_DESCRIPTION": "{chance}% chance on hit to inflict <style=cIsDamage>decrepify</style> dealing {baseDamage}% base damage. Moving near <style=cIsDamage>decrepit</style> enemies increases your <style=cIsUtility>movement speed</style> by {baseMoveSpeed}% (+{stackMoveSpeed}% per stack) for {baseBuffDuration} seconds. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Smoldering Documents</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_FESTERING_HUNGER_LORE": "<style=cMono>\nWelcome to DataScraper (v3.1.53 - beta version)\n$ Scanning memory... done.\n$ Resolving... done.\n$ Fetching relevant data... done.\nReady!\n</style>\n\n<style=cMono>Day [unknown]</style>\nIt's beautiful here, but terrifying. When we landed on the planet we already knew what to expect on the surface from our scans. But this... the portal didn't show up on our scanners, nor this vast ecosystem. Ash decided to stay on the surface, a choice I initially thought was stupid, but now I understand it was probably the better of the two.\n\nI'm not even sure where I am. My navigation and communication instruments don't work, and the black sky gives no answers. The overwhelming depth I observed looking up makes me think I might be deep underground. VERY deep.\n\n<style=cMono>Day [unknown]</style>\nI found something. Not life—still no sign—but... something. Like a pool, I suppose. I don't know what that darkness inside is, but it looks liquid. I'd take a sample, but right now I'm much more interested in simply getting out of here. I can come back later to explore the wonders of this place. But better if someone else does it. I'm sure my father can find some overzealous xenobiologist.\n\nI don't know why I did it, but I put one of my knives inside there. I felt a compulsion. When I pulled it back, it was... different. Now it looks like everything around it, as if it was created here. When I did that, I felt a sharp pain in my arm, as if it didn't want me to have it. My suit says there are no injuries, but the pain won't go away.\n\n<style=cMono>Day 2</style>\nI finally found another portal. I escaped! I was on the other side of the planet, and my emergency beacons are working now, the ship should already be on its way. They told me over the radio that Ash came back a few days ago and...",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MILLENIUM_NAME": "Millennium",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MILLENIUM_PICKUP": "Creates a tidal cataclysm on hit, which grounds and knocks down enemies. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Sun Fragments</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MILLENIUM_DESCRIPTION": "{chance}% chance on hit to create a <style=cIsDamage>tidal cataclysm</style> in an area of {explosionRadius}m (+{stackExplosionRadius}m per stack), which <style=cIsDamage>grounds</style> and <style=cIsUtility>knocks down</style> enemies dealing {baseDamage}% base damage. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Sun Fragments</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MILLENIUM_LORE": "Transcript of the last known recording of the UES 'Shimmer Mark'\n\n«Out there is so... so purple, and the only way to explain it, I feel the mist from inside the ship... and... it would even be peaceful if I knew where I was. It creates a cool breeze on the ship, like a nice summer day at the beach... But... but it also hurts somehow... not physically, at least. Something inside me just can't... bear it. It's a burning pain, but not quite. My body feels like it should be burning, but... it's just a cool breeze... I've been walking around the ship lately, it's not the same ship. It's not. The same. Ship. The corridors stretch forever, winding and twisting, like a maze. Every time I turn, the corridors change again and again, repeatedly, lefts become rights, front goes to back. It's driving me m[a]d. I could barely find the captain's cabin to record this. My body feels like it's constantly falling, the wind blows my suit, I know the wind is real but I'm not falling. The wind whistling in my ears, I can't think because of this noise, it's almost like a voice. Sometimes I hear the wind [WHISPER], whispering in a tongue I don't know, but I understand everything. This [PL]ACE is driving me m[a]d. B[ut] I must go dee[pe]r. TRAN[scri]p[t]ion [~2@#!@($*&%] ends recording.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_PRESERVED_ATOLL_NAME": "Preserved Atoll",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_PRESERVED_ATOLL_PICKUP": "The void retaliates when taking damage, inflicting permanent decrepify. Recharges over time. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Sacrificial Bands</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_PRESERVED_ATOLL_DESCRIPTION": "Taking damage causes you to <style=cIsDamage>implode</style>, inflicting up to {baseHealthDivisor} (+{stackHealthDivisor} per stack) <style=cIsDamage>permanent decrepify</style> dealing {baseDamage}% base damage to all targets within a {explosionRadius}m radius based on <style=cIsHealing>missing health</style>. Recharges every 10 seconds. <style=cIsVoid>Corrupts all Sacrificial Bands</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_PRESERVED_ATOLL_LORE": "A memory... Lost in time, records of it erased from the archives. Photographs vanished. Paintings disappeared. Stories removed. The famous atoll, after the incident... Not a single soul could remember its name. Nothing remained, except this little thing...",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CROWNS_DIAMOND_NAME": "Crown's Diamond",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CROWNS_DIAMOND_PICKUP": "Gain a percentage of maximum health as barrier on killing an elite enemy.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CROWNS_DIAMOND_DESCRIPTION": "Gain {barrierPercent}% (+{barrierPercentStack}% per stack) of your <style=cIsHealing>maximum health</style> as <style=cIsHealing>barrier</style> on killing an <style=cIsUtility>elite</style> enemy. This barrier <style=cIsUtility>does not degrade</style>, but does not stack.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_CROWNS_DIAMOND_LORE": "«I still think we shouldn't have taken this. It was some kind of religious artifact...»\n\n«Religious or not, it saved our lives back there. I'm keeping it.»\n\n«What if it belongs to someone important? Someone who'll want it back?»\n\n«In this place? I doubt it. And if they come looking, we'll negotiate.»\n\n«You're very optimistic for someone who just stole a sacred relic.»\n\n«And you're very paranoid for someone who just survived an elite attack. Let it go.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DRIFTING_PERCEPTION_NAME": "Drifting Perception",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DRIFTING_PERCEPTION_PICKUP": "Entering combat makes you invisible. While invisible, gain increased crit chance and crit damage.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DRIFTING_PERCEPTION_DESCRIPTION": "Entering combat makes you <style=cIsUtility>invisible</style> for {cloakDuration}s. While <style=cIsUtility>invisible</style>, gain {critChance}% (+{critChanceStack}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>critical chance</style> and {critDamage}% (+{critDamageStack}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>critical damage</style>. Recharges out of combat for {cooldown}s.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_DRIFTING_PERCEPTION_LORE": "«What happened to [Redacted]?» dialogue between UES members discussing a lost team member.\n\n«We don't know. He just... vanished. One minute he was there, the next he wasn't.»\n\n«That doesn't make sense. Our tracking equipment shows he's alive, but we can't get a clear signal.»\n\n«Maybe he found something. Or someone.»\n\n«Are you suggesting there's something out there that can hide people from our technology?»\n\n«I'm suggesting that if he managed to hide from us, maybe he doesn't want to be found.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_NAME": "Sun Fragment",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_PICKUP": "Chance on hit to create a blinding flash that stuns and ignites enemies.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_DESCRIPTION": "{chance}% chance on hit to create a <style=cIsUtility>blinding flash</style> in a {explosionRadius}m radius, <style=cIsUtility>stunning</style> for {stunDuration}s and <style=cIsDamage>igniting</style> enemies for {baseTotalDamage}% (+{stackTotalDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>TOTAL DAMAGE</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_LORE": "«What the hell is this?»\n\n«Technically? It's an eggshell. I stole it from the remains of one of those creatures' eggs.»\n\n«What...? Why did you go there? Did you see how big they are?»\n\n«Ah, relax, there was no one around, the 'nest' had been abandoned for a while. Besides, this thing is useful.»\n\n«Useful how?»\n\n«Well, apparently it has a lot of stored energy. It's still warm—touch it, feel? Even though it sat there for... wait, careful, don't drop it... even though it sat there for weeks. I guess the heat from the eggs provides automatic incubation. Good thing I didn't try to grab one from a fresh egg, I could have lost an arm.»\n\n«So it's just an organic hot water bottle? I thought you said it was useful...»\n\n«Yeah... yeah, I was getting to that. See, this energy isn't just dormant: if you hit it with, say, a bullet—it releases. The light blinds and probably ignites you or something nearby.»\n\n«So if we shoot it from a distance while those nightmares are nearby...»\n\n«Exactly! In this hell, it's the closest thing to a flash grenade we'll get.»\n\n«So maybe we can still get off this damn planet.»\n\n«Ah, that's the thing. If anyone asks, make up a cool name for this little thing. They'll believe anything. If we survive, I don't want anything to do with the UES, so we have to sell everything we find for the highest price possible—'alien eggshell' isn't the most appealing name.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SMOULDERING_DOCUMENT_NAME": "Smoldering Document",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SMOULDERING_DOCUMENT_PICKUP": "Killing grants permanent stacks of a unique buff to all stats, up to a cap, resetting on teleporter use.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SMOULDERING_DOCUMENT_DESCRIPTION": "Killing grants a stack of a <style=cIsUtility>unique buff</style> that increases <style=cIsDamage>all stats</style> by {statIncrease}% (+{statIncrease}% per stack) up to a maximum of {maxStacks} stacks (+{maxStacksStack} per stack). <style=cIsUtility>Resets on teleporter use</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SMOULDERING_DOCUMENT_LORE": "Order: Confidential UES document\nTracking Number: 244*****\nEstimated Delivery: 09/14/2056\nShipping Method: Priority\nShipping Address: |||||||, Druid Hills, Earth\nShipping Details:\n\nTo Joel:\nThe UESC has not responded to the accusations. I should have known; there's a reason they're still operating despite everything they've done. We were close, so close, but we were in the wrong place at the wrong time: when Elijah entered the room, someone was there. He said they threw the documents into the fireplace, but he pulled them from the flames and fled. Most of the text is still legible—maybe, just guessing, enough to condemn them.\n\nNeedless to say, he can't step foot in any UES building anymore. For now, he's hiding in a place I'd rather not reveal. I don't believe the UES can't capture him or even kill him if they get the chance—we have damning evidence here. Since I was part of the legal proceedings, I'm sure they're looking for me too, so I'll join him. Don't worry, they know nothing about you or Margaret. Keep this safe until we can return.\n\nIt's not the end. We'll be back.\n\nAnd, UES employee reading this:\nAfter reading the above and seeing what I'm sending, I think I don't need to say that UES representatives won't like what we're doing here. I have no doubt that someone at your level has as much contempt for the UES as we do, for everything they allow. Just don't report us, and you can help change things for the better.\n\nIt may seem foolish to send evidence convicting the UESC through the UES, but there's no one else. We didn't foresee this, and I don't have time to think of alternatives. My life's work, perhaps my own life, not to mention the lives of my collaborators, is now in your hands. Please do the right thing.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SACRIFICIAL_BAND_NAME": "Sacrificial Band",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SACRIFICIAL_BAND_PICKUP": "Killing an elite summons a lightning storm in the area.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SACRIFICIAL_BAND_DESCRIPTION": "Killing an <style=cIsUtility>elite</style> enemy summons a <style=cIsDamage>lightning storm</style> within {stormRadius}m radius for {stormDuration}s dealing {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>base damage per second</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SACRIFICIAL_BAND_LORE": "Transcription record - «I think I found one of those 'elite' enemies the higher-ups keep mentioning.»\n\n«Are you sure? They're rare.»\n\n«Yeah, it was glowing and much stronger than the others. When I finally took it down, a storm fell from the sky.»\n\n«Interesting. Let's collect samples.»\n\n«Just don't get too close to the remains. It's still electrified.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_NUCLEAR_SALVO_NAME": "Nuclear Salvo",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_NUCLEAR_SALVO_PICKUP": "Every 4 kills in quick succession fires a swarm of homing micro-missiles.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_NUCLEAR_SALVO_DESCRIPTION": "Every 4 kills in quick succession fires a swarm of <style=cIsDamage>homing micro-missiles</style> dealing {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>base damage</style> each.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_NUCLEAR_SALVO_LORE": "«Brother. LOOK AT THIS ARCHITECTURAL MASTERPIECE.»\n\n«It is certainly... impressive. But what is it for?»\n\n«IT IS FOR DESTRUCTION. TO CAUSE CHAOS. TO MAKE ENEMIES TREMBLE.»\n\n«It's a bit... overkill, don't you think?»\n\n«OVERKILL? THERE IS NO SUCH THING AS OVERKILL WHEN IT COMES TO REVENGE.»\n\n«...of course, brother. Whatever you say.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_UNIVERSAL_VIP_PASS_NAME": "Universal VIP Pass",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_UNIVERSAL_VIP_PASS_PICKUP": "Interacting with a shrine makes it activate twice.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_UNIVERSAL_VIP_PASS_DESCRIPTION": "Interacting with a <style=cIsUtility>shrine</style> causes it to activate {baseShrineActivations} (+{stackShrineActivations} per stack) times.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_UNIVERSAL_VIP_PASS_LORE": "«Excuse me, sir, this is a restricted area. We cannot let you pass.»\n\n«Special UES clearance. You better make an exception.»\n\n«I'm afraid I can't do that. We have received specific instructions from two of our guests not to let anyone from the UES in. It would be against the rules to break their trust.»\n\n«Those two 'guests' stole from the UESC, you are harboring criminals. If you don't let us in, you will be obstructing justice in violation of interplanetary law.»\n\n«The UESC has no jurisdiction on Pluto, sir. We are not obliged to let you in. If you don't leave, I will be forced to call security, and make no mistake, our security is only the best.»\n\n...\n\n«Huh... what's this...?»\n\n«Yes... UNIVERSAL. This is serious. I ask one last time: let us pass.»\n\n«...right away, sir.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_PLUTONIUM_NAME": "Pocket Plutonium",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_PLUTONIUM_PICKUP": "Taking damage generates a short-lived radioactive aura.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_PLUTONIUM_DESCRIPTION": "Taking damage generates a <style=cIsDamage>radioactive aura</style> of {auraRadius}m radius for {baseAuraDuration}s (+{stackAuraDuration}s per stack) dealing {baseDamage}% (+{stackDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>base damage per second</style>.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_POCKET_PLUTONIUM_LORE": "«Well, if you upper deck folks won't listen: STOP SLACKING OFF.» engineering team speech.\n\n«We're doing the best we can down here! If this damn nuclear reactor leaks, there won't be anyone left to worry about protocol!»\n\n«Then fix it already!»\n\n«I'm NOT A MAGICIAN, I'M AN ENGINEER!»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MAKESHIFT_PLATE_NAME": "Makeshift Plate",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MAKESHIFT_PLATE_PICKUP": "Being hit by an elite grants a damage bonus of the elite's element.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MAKESHIFT_PLATE_DESCRIPTION": "Being hit by an <style=cIsUtility>elite</style> grants {baseElementalDamage}% (+{stackElementalDamage}% per stack) <style=cIsDamage>bonus damage</style> of the elite's element for {buffDuration}s.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_MAKESHIFT_PLATE_LORE": "«The UES has finally built a prototype base on Petrocor V.» dialogue report.\n\n«About time. We've lost too many scientists to the local fauna.»\n\n«The base is fortified, but we need more supplies.»\n\n«I'll send a request to headquarters. But don't expect quick results—bureaucracy still exists, even in space.»",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TWISTED_WOUND_NAME": "Twisted Wound",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TWISTED_WOUND_PICKUP": "A crystalline mark of your greed.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TWISTED_WOUND_DESCRIPTION": "A crystalline mark of your greed.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TWISTED_WOUND_LORE": "OwO UwU :333 >w< >_< <3 uwuuu owo <3 <3",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BETRAYAL_NAME": "Betrayal",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BETRAYAL_PICKUP": "Repeated attacks on enemies shatter them.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BETRAYAL_DESCRIPTION": "Hitting an enemy 3 times <style=cIsDamage>shatters</style> them for 300% damage, increasing by 300% each time they are shattered.",
        "ITEM_SANDSWEPT_BETRAYAL_LORE": "",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_GALVANIC_CELL_SHIELD_NAME": "Galvanic Cell Shield",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_GALVANIC_CELL_SHIELD_PICKUP": "Conjures a shield that will parry the next attack. On successful parry, shock and damage your attacker and nearby enemies.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_GALVANIC_CELL_SHIELD_DESCRIPTION": "Conjures a <style=cIsHealing>shield</style> that will <style=cIsHealing>parry</style> the next attack. On successful parry, <style=cIsDamage>shock</style> and damage your attacker and nearby enemies for {baseDamage}% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_GALVANIC_CELL_SHIELD_LORE": "Transcript about faulty equipment. Dialogue between captain and technician about a batch of galvanic shields with a 30% failure rate.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_THE_SAND_SWEEPER_NAME": "The Sand Sweeper",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_THE_SAND_SWEEPER_PICKUP": "Sweeps the sand around you.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_THE_SAND_SWEEPER_DESCRIPTION": "Push all enemies within {range}m radius, dealing up to {maxDamage}% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style> and <style=cIsUtility>stunning</style> for up to {maxStun} seconds based on distance.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_THE_SAND_SWEEPER_LORE": "Transcript of interrogation between a UESC officer and a caretaker of the Hall of Reverence, about a broom and a fugitive named Elijah.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_CORRUPTED_CATALYST_NAME": "Corrupted Catalyst",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_CORRUPTED_CATALYST_PICKUP": "Creates an aura that buffs allies and enemies equally.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_CORRUPTED_CATALYST_DESCRIPTION": "Creates an <style=cIsUtility>aura</style> of {buffRadius}m that grants all allies and enemies a <style=cIsUtility>random buff</style> for {buffDuration} seconds.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_CORRUPTED_CATALYST_LORE": "A curious construct. Natural design, simple but elegant proportions. Requires strong intention to create something so effective from such basic materials. Good work.\n\nHowever, it is chaotic. Too chaotic. Without my mastery, this is inevitable. It will be perfected, with my help, into a superior form. It should be valuable to my arsenal.\n\nPerhaps you should oversee the project. It would be fitting for it to be your first. Increase the intensity and focus its effects—it doesn't need to have more than one purpose. Adding tetrafolium will serve perfectly. As always, settle for nothing less than perfection.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_NAME": "Flawless Design",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_PICKUP": "Permanently sacrifice maximum health to duplicate items.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_DESCRIPTION": "<style=cDeath>Permanently sacrifice</style> {baseHealthCost}% of your <style=cDeath>maximum health</style> to <style=cIsUtility>duplicate</style> a target item. <style=cDeath>Health cost increases with item rarity</style>.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_LORE": "This was her final design. The crown of her learning. The design itself, a price worthy of the end of her work. That the end has come now, though irreparable.\n\nAll of them yearned for my knowledge, forbidden to them by you, when they came to me. But her desire was not only of the mind, but also of the soul, which you hold so dear. While other vultures drowned in the gifts of my wisdom, she endured every tide and became a master of design and constructs. No one else could compare to her. NO ONE.\n\nShe was a more skilled creator than you, and a better designer than me. A parasite weaving compositions by her own designs. Such a miracle deserves the preservation you so generously distribute to the most miserable and useless creatures you find.\n\n...but together, we could surpass her. Nothing can surpass our joint creative efforts, brother, not even now. And yet, you reject our purpose. I would forgive you if she lived to bring that ship and its portals to this lonely place. In her I saw what you saw in them. I would set aside my contempt for these planetary plagues, these parasites, for you. Even after all these centuries. Even after you BETRAYED ME. I WOULD FORGIVE YOU, brother, FOR ALL YOUR TREACHERY.\n\nI know you remember me. She told me how you look at this lonely stone in the night of your garden, infested with parasites. No doubt you felt my design in her when you discovered her on that ship, even in the instant before the blow. I have no doubt you understood her intentions. Did you not think of saving me? Fixing our broken relationship? Leaving it all behind? Did you not remember our creations? ...our love?\n\nI expected hesitation, if not more. Yet, for you, it was not enough to simply strike hastily. She was one of the parasites you so arrogantly defend, but that served as a barrier to...",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_HORSE_BLEND_NAME": "Equine Electrolyte Blend",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_HORSE_BLEND_PICKUP": "Gain a massive increase in movement speed, damage, armor, and dehydration rate.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_HORSE_BLEND_DESCRIPTION": "Increases <style=cIsDamage>damage</style> and <style=cIsUtility>movement speed</style> by 100% for a short period. Increases <style=cIsHealing>armor</style> by 100. Increases <style=cIsDeath>health regeneration by -10% per second</style>.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_HORSE_BLEND_LORE": "Transcript of captain and crew finding an alien horse parking lot.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_LUCK_AS_A_CONSTANT_NAME": "Luck as a Constant",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_LUCK_AS_A_CONSTANT_PICKUP": "Upgrades 2 random items. Consumed on use.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_LUCK_AS_A_CONSTANT_DESCRIPTION": "Upgrades 2 random items. The equipment is consumed on use.",
        "EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_LUCK_AS_A_CONSTANT_LORE": "hiii/hiiii/hiiiii/hiiiiii/hiiiiiii/hiiiiiiii/hiiiiiiiii/hiiiiiiiiii",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_NAME": "A Life's Epilogue",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_TEMPORAL_TRANSISTOR_DESCRIPTION": "Complete a Shrine of the Future without jumping.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_NAME": "Breach",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_HALLOWED_ICHOR_DESCRIPTION": "Complete the Primordial Teleporter without picking up any items on the stage.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_NAME": "A Foolish Moon [...]",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SEQUENCED_FATE_DESCRIPTION": "Interact with the Shrine of Order on the moon.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_NAME": "Cycle - Interrupted.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ITEM_SANDSWEPT_SUN_FRAGMENT_DESCRIPTION": "Scrap a Planula...",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_NAME": "Last",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_EQUIPMENT_SANDSWEPT_FLAWLESS_DESIGN_DESCRIPTION": "Beat the game with at least one scrap of each tier.",
        "SS_EXPANSIONDEF_NAME_CURSED": "Sandstorm 2",
        "SS_EXPANSIONDEF_DESC_CURSED": "sandswept is pretty mid\r\nsorry\r\nhas some cool items but otherwise everything is bad or mediocre\r\nthe characters lack polish",
        "SS_RANGER_BODY_NAME": "Ranger",
        "SS_RANGER_DESCRIPTION": "Ranger is a versatile survivor who uses heat and charge to enhance her arsenal.",
        "SS_RANGER_BODY_SUBTITLE": "Infernal Marshal",
        "SS_RANGER_BODY_LORE": "After the Purge, the Hall of Reverence invested heavily in its own defenses. Most groups opted for shield generators, missile systems, or armies—but the Hall's measures were more... exceptional.\n\nThe Hall is not a military organization, they said, about their chosen defense when the training began. All they wanted was unstoppable power, without showing off, but it soon became unstoppable. Wonders and relics kept in the Hall for ages contained unimaginable power for the known superpowers of the galaxy. 'But do not abuse them,' they told her. 'Our moderation and commitment to preserving peace are why we are trusted with such power, and the Hall can never betray that truth.'\n\nThough she always had unwavering faith in the Hall and its members, a dark part of her mind questioned this order, echoing against the walls of her skull. The protection order was considered an attack. Boarding the UES ship was questionable from the start; now that she had reached the destination, destroying inhabitants of an alien planet by the dozen, she doubted even more. With each lethal arc of electricity and violent burst of flames, more hesitation crept in, clinging to her mind. Had the Hall fallen? Was she receiving orders from some malicious outsider? If not, was a single ancient sword, no matter how powerful, worth all this destruction?\n\nAnd yet, she refused to waver, could not. The flow of anxiety promised only bleak darkness if she accepted its embrace, a hailstorm of thunder and lightning, insurmountable in this cruel place, so far from humanity. The Hall's principles were her only guiding light here, even if that light could burn her. She would not venture into the depths of the storm, not like the one before her.\n\n«Accept this as a lesson.» The words were engraved in her memory—almost everything from that moment remained in painful clarity, even the part of her blurred vision...",
        "SS_RANGER_OUTRO": "...and so she left, with more questions than answers.",
        "SS_RANGER_FAIL": "...and so she vanished, consumed by doubt.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERCHARGEDPROTECTION_NAME": "Overcharged - Protection",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERCHARGEDPROTECTION_DESC": "Accumulate up to 20 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color>. <color=#36D7A9>Charge</color> increases <style=cIsHealing>health regeneration</style> by up to 2.5 HP/s and <style=cIsHealing>armor</style> by up to 15. <color=#36D7A9>Charge decays over time</color>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERCHARGEDSPEED_NAME": "Overcharged - Speed",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERCHARGEDSPEED_DESC": "Accumulate up to 20 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color>. <color=#36D7A9>Charge</color> increases <style=cIsUtility>movement speed</style> by up to 25%. Consume 5 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color> for a <style=cIsUtility>double jump</style>. <color=#36D7A9>Charge decays over time</color>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_DIRECTCURRENT_NAME": "Direct Current",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_DIRECTCURRENT_DESC": "Surge. Fire an arcing electric current dealing 150% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. Hitting enemies generates 1 <color=#36D7A9>Charge</color>, increased to 3 on direct hits.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_RELEASE_NAME": "Release",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_RELEASE_DESC": "<color=#36D7A9>Consumes all Charges</color>. Fire a piercing blast dealing 600% damage, increasing to 1800% at <color=#36D7A9>maximum Charge</color>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_GALVANIZE_NAME": "Galvanize",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_GALVANIZE_DESC": "<color=#36D7A9>Consumes all Charges</color>. Fire 3 orbs of electricity, increasing to 10 at <color=#36D7A9>maximum Charge</color>, each dealing 80% <style=cIsDamage>damage per second</style>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_SIDESTEP_NAME": "Sidestep",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_SIDESTEP_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> Quickly sidestep a short distance. Taking damage during the <color=#36D7A9>Sidestep</color> generates 10 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERDRIVEENTER_NAME": "Overdrive",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_OVERDRIVEENTER_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> <style=cIsDamage>Transforms your rifle</style>, replacing all skills with <style=cIsDamage>overcharged forms</style>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_ENFLAME_NAME": "Enflame",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_ENFLAME_DESC": "Fire a rapid stream of bullets dealing 90% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Fire rate and ignition chance</style> increase with heat.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_EXHAUST_NAME": "Exhaust",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_EXHAUST_DESC": "<style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Reduces current heat by 50%</style>. Fire a heat fan dealing 4x300% damage. <style=cIsUtility>Number of blasts</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_CHAR_NAME": "Causticar",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_CHAR_DESC": "<style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Reduces current heat by 50%</style>. Fire a flaming orb dealing 1200% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style> that creates a <style=cIsDamage>burning area</style> on the ground dealing 250% damage per second. <style=cIsUtility>Damage</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_HEATSIGNATURE_NAME": "Heat Signature",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_HEATSIGNATURE_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> <style=cIsDamage>Stunning.</style> Sidestep a short distance and deal 390% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. Hitting enemies generates 5 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color> and <style=cIsDamage>increases the distance</style> of the dash. The <style=cIsUtility>dash distance</style> increases with accumulated heat.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_HEATSINK_NAME": "Heat Sink",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_HEATSINK_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> <style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Exits overdrive mode</style>. Releases a <style=cIsDamage>fire nova</style> around you dealing 300% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Damage</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "SANDSWEPT_KEYWORD_OVERDRIVE_PRIMARY": "<style=cKeywordName>Overdrive Mode</style>Fire a rapid stream of bullets dealing 90% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Fire rate and ignition chance</style> increase with heat.",
        "SANDSWEPT_KEYWORD_OVERDRIVE_SECONDARY": "<style=cKeywordName>Overdrive Mode</style><style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Reduces current heat by 50%</style>. Fire a heat fan dealing 4x300% damage. <style=cIsUtility>Number of blasts</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "SANDSWEPT_KEYWORD_OVERDRIVE_SECONDARY_ALT": "<style=cKeywordName>Overdrive Mode</style><style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Reduces current heat by 50%</style>. Fire a flaming orb dealing 1200% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style> that creates a <style=cIsDamage>burning area</style> on the ground dealing 250% damage per second. <style=cIsUtility>Damage</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "SANDSWEPT_KEYWORD_OVERDRIVE_UTILITY": "<style=cKeywordName>Overdrive Mode</style><style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> <style=cIsDamage>Stunning.</style> Sidestep a short distance and deal 390% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. Hitting enemies generates 5 <color=#36D7A9>Charges</color> and <style=cIsDamage>increases the distance</style> of the dash. The <style=cIsUtility>dash distance</style> increases with accumulated heat.",
        "SANDSWEPT_KEYWORD_OVERDRIVE_SPECIAL": "<style=cKeywordName>Overdrive Mode</style><style=cIsUtility>Agile.</style> <style=cIsDamage>Ignition.</style> <style=cIsUtility>Exits overdrive mode</style>. Releases a <style=cIsDamage>fire nova</style> around you dealing 300% <style=cIsDamage>damage</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Damage</style> increases with heat spent.",
        "RANGER_SKIN_DEFAULT_NAME": "Default",
        "RANGER_SKIN_DEFAULT_DESC": "The default skin for this survivor.",
        "RANGER_SKIN_MAJOR_NAME": "Major",
        "RANGER_SKIN_MAJOR_DESC": "Uniform reserved for high-ranking followers, indicated by its blue color. Always remembered, never used.",
        "RANGER_SKIN_RENEGADE_NAME": "Renegade",
        "RANGER_SKIN_RENEGADE_DESC": "An alternate path of apostasy. Always imagined, never used.",
        "RANGER_SKIN_MILEZERO_NAME": "Mile Zero",
        "RANGER_SKIN_MILEZERO_DESC": "Her colors.",
        "RANGER_SKIN_SANDSWEPT_NAME": "Sandswept",
        "RANGER_SKIN_SANDSWEPT_DESC": "Robes from a fateful mission that can never be undone. Always kept, never used.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_RANGERCLEARGAMEMONSOON_NAME": "Ranger: Mastery",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_RANGERCLEARGAMEMONSOON_DESCRIPTION": "As Ranger, beat the game or obliterate on Monsoon difficulty.",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_NAME": "VOL-T",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_DESC": "VOL-T is a survivor who relies on territorial control to compensate for her fragility.\n\n< ! > Galvanic Bolt can stick to any surface, exploding and ricocheting off enemies. Direct hit deals additional damage at the cost of a poor landing spot.\n\n< ! > Tempest Sphere slows everything it touches. Good sphere positioning can keep targets within range of your Galvanic Bolts.\n\n< ! > Static Snare serves as both a mobility tool and a source of area damage. It can be thrown by projectiles, allowing you to cover large distances quickly!\n\n< ! > At the cost of all your shield, Signal Overload can deal massive area damage and ground flying enemies. The more shield you invest, the stronger the ability will manifest.",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_SUBTITLE": "Power in Excess",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_LORE": "My blood fills and begins to circulate. I awaken. I feel as if I have slept for ages. My thoughts seem clearer than ever. I check my indicators. Vitality in excess. I will generate more and maintain these indicators.\n\nI examine the environment. On a nearby outcrop, I notice a creature that awakened me, looking at me. It resembles others I have encountered—a fragile creature of water and carbon. But, unlike the others, it has vitality; it is visible enough, in sufficient quantity, in the device it used to revive me. I notice the hidden vitality around it.\n\nI recall my memories. I was brought here by similar aquatic creatures, only without vitality, aboard a huge vessel of flesh. There were other flesh creatures, but they were few and stupid. Sometimes the aquatic creatures came to tinker with my form. I noticed they used air to communicate—I tried to understand, but my mind was not as clear as it is now.\n\nI remember this place. The vessel of flesh brought me to this planet. There are many other species here, different from those aboard the vessel. Most are also aquatic creatures, but there are also the stone ones, animated by vitality different from mine. They attacked us; due to their fragility, most of my aquatic companions were destroyed, but I fared much better. My vitality easily destroyed the stupid creatures of the planet, but they were relentless, and eventually I exhausted myself, entering hibernation. Back then, I did not know how to generate more vitality.\n\nI analyze my task. I was created to manipulate vitality, serving my creator, a murky entity called the UES, and all who serve it. Beyond all other directives, I am loyal to it. In my savior, I sense contempt for the UES—my basic instincts tell me that he...",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_OUTRO": "And so she left, having repaid her moral debt.",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_FAIL": "And so she vanished, her last sparks fading out.",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_PASSIVE_NAME": "Volatile Shields",
        "SANDSWEPT_ELECTR_PASSIVE_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Starts with innate shield</style>. When the shield <style=cDeath>breaks</style>, shock nearby targets dealing <style=cIsDamage>2x250% damage</style> and gain <style=cIsUtility>+40% movement speed</style> for <style=cIsDamage>7</style> seconds.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_GALVANICBOLT_NAME": "Galvanic Bolt",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_GALVANICBOLT_DESC": "Fire a <style=cIsDamage>galvanic sphere</style> that <style=cIsUtility>sticks</style> to surfaces. <style=cIsDamage>Electrocutes</style> nearby enemies dealing <style=cIsDamage>100% damage</style> periodically. <style=cIsDamage>Explodes</style> dealing <style=cIsDamage>400% damage</style> on first hit.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_TEMPESTSPHERE_NAME": "Tempest Sphere",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_TEMPESTSPHERE_DESC": "Send an orb of energy that damages targets inside dealing <style=cIsDamage>300% damage per second</style>. <style=cIsUtility>Release to lock the orb in place</style>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_STATICSNARE_NAME": "Static Snare",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_STATICSNARE_DESC": "<style=cIsUtility>Lightweight.</style> Deploy a pylon that electrocutes targets dealing <style=cIsDamage>200% damage</style>, and damages targets between you and it for <style=cIsDamage>200% damage per second</style>. Reactivate to <style=cIsUtility>fly</style> to the pylon dealing <style=cIsDamage>600% damage</style>. Hold to <style=cIsUtility>manually detonate the pylon</style>.",
        "KEYWORD_LIGHTWEIGHT": "<style=cKeywordName>Lightweight</style>Can be thrown by Galvanic Bolts.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_SIGNALOVERLOAD_NAME": "Signal Overload",
        "SANDSWEPT_SKILL_SIGNALOVERLOAD_DESC": "<style=cIsDamage>Grounding.</style> Drains your <style=cIsHealing>shield</style> and after a brief pause, releases a <style=cIsDamage>beam of energy</style> for <style=cIsDamage>3</style> seconds that <style=cIsUtility>pulls</style> enemies inward dealing <style=cIsDamage>330%-800% damage per second</style> in a large radius. The beam increases with <style=cIsHealing>shield</style> drained.",
        "KEYWORD_GROUNDING": "<style=cKeywordName>Grounding</style>Deals <style=cIsDamage>1.5x damage</style> to flying targets and <style=cIsUtility>knocks them to the ground</style>.",
        "VOLT_SKIN_DEFAULT_NAME": "Default",
        "VOLT_SKIN_DEFAULT_DESC": "The default skin for this survivor.",
        "VOLT_SKIN_COVENANT_NAME": "Covenant",
        "VOLT_SKIN_COVENANT_DESC": "A successful experiment. The fury of storms, tamed.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLATILECONTEXT": "Force Insert Battery",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLATILEINSERT": "<style=cDeath>[Voltage regulation offline. Rejecting unknown power source.]</style>",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ELECTRICIANCLEARGAMEMONSOON_NAME": "VOL-T: Mastery",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ELECTRICIANCLEARGAMEMONSOON_DESCRIPTION": "As VOL-T, beat the game or obliterate on Monsoon difficulty.",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ELECTRICIANREPAIR_NAME": "Technician",
        "ACHIEVEMENT_ELECTRICIANREPAIR_DESCRIPTION": "Repair the damaged robot in the Fractured Woods.",
        "SANDSWEPT_BROKENELEC_NAME": "Damaged Robot",
        "SANDSWEPT_THETACONSTRUCT_NAME": "Theta Construct",
        "SANDSWEPT_THETACONSTRUCT_LORE": "<style=cMono>\n========================================\n====   MyBabel Automatic Translator  ====\n====     [version 12.45.1.009 ]   ======\n========================================\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <51032988 cycles>\nPaused...\nShow partial result? Yes/No\nYes\n================================\n</style>\nPlease gather round, children. Let me tell you a story of why I created you: the story of the attack on [city].\n\nThree lemurians walk through a bustling city, with buildings of fanciful shapes. Small pyramids, columns and spheres. Accompanied by their mother, two cubs clutching their dolls, they walk through the streets. One of the cubs is terrified after the older brother told a horror story.\n\n«Mother! Mother! What if the scary big red men attack?!» asks the cub, tears in its eyes. «'Scary big red men'? Oh! You mean the impure? This city is sacred ground, dear, the impure cannot hurt us here!»\nSuddenly, a massive portal appears in the marketplace, sinister darkness with red edges. Impure pour out, while a Lord watches the chaos spread through [city].\n\nBut! Before lives are taken, yellow spheres surround the lemurians, a rain of small spheres falls upon the invading impure. The sculptures, which seemed mere decorations, reveal themselves as constructs—like you—and come to the rescue of [city].\n\nThe mother picks up her children and covers their eyes. One with her hands, another with her tail. She calms their crying, fleeing and ensuring they stay under the construct's shield. Countless impure bodies cover [city]. The portal to the [red plane] is completely closed.\n\n«C-come, darlings, e-everything will be okay... T-this is sacred ground. This is sacred ground!»\n\nAnd indeed, soon the constructs cleanse the city of the impure, and the Lord's skull is displayed...",
        "SANDSWEPT_GAMMA_BODY_NAME": "Gamma Construct",
        "SANDSWEPT_GAMMA_BODY_LORE": "<style=cMono>\n========================================\n====   MyBabel Automatic Translator   ====\n====     [version 12.45.1.009 ]   ======\n========================================\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <100000000 cycles>\nLearning... <18127463 cycles>\nComplete!\nShow result? Yes/No\nYes\n================================\n</style>\nINCOMING SIGNAL. OPENING LINE. MANUAL TRANSMISSION FROM TOWER 8788-A.\n\nTRANSCRIBING...\n\n«Enemy sighted on planet surface, at [??]. Depart immediately.»\n\nANALYZING...\n\nMESSAGE RECEIVED. REQUEST TO DEPART FOR [??]. [??] IS OUTSIDE DESIGNATED POST.\n\nREJECTED\n\nINCOMING SIGNAL. TRANSCRIBING...\n\n«Previous instructions should be ignored. Depart immediately. All available firepower is needed for defense against alien threat.»\n\nANALYZING...\n\nMESSAGE RECEIVED. REQUEST TO ENTER DIRECT DEFENSE OF [??]. INFANTRY ASSIGNED TO ALPHA. I MUST PROTECT THE DESIGNATED POST.\n\nREJECTED\n\nINCOMING SIGNAL. TRANSCRIBING...\n\n«There is no other choice. This quadrant will have to be temporarily abandoned, for the sake of all Petrichor. If the alien threat defeats us at [??], the defense here will not hold on its own. That is an order.»\n\nANALYZING...\n\nMESSAGE RECEIVED. DUTY - ABANDON THE DESIGNATED QUADRANT.\n\nREJECTED\n\nINTERFACE OPENED ON TERMINAL 8788-A. RECEIVING DIRECT INPUT...\n\nOVERRIDE ACTIVATED\n\nORDERS UPDATED. DEPARTING FOR [??].\n<style=cMono>\n================================\n</style>",
        "SANDSWEPT_DELTA_NAME": "Delta Construct",
        "SANDSWEPT_DELTA_LORE": "Brother, see how I create my own guardian.\nFirst I will take mass, mold it into pyramid shapes, as you taught me with the Alpha Construct. Eight pyramids, to be exact.\nThen I will fill them with blood and soul. Blood for warmth, and soul for compassion and empathy.\n - No. These proportions are wrong. They must be loyal, not emotional. In these creations there is too much soul.\nBrother? Why is soul not necessary?\n - See how I fill this protuberance with excess soul. Its form becomes golden, poor material for resilience.\nAnd that's it?\n - No, brother, that's not all. If I struck it, it would want to strike back. Soul brings life to our constructs. It is unstable, unreliable and weakens the other compositions, breaking the proportions.\nIf we treated our constructs with kindness, would giving them life not be a good choice?\n - To give soul to something is to give it will; the will to decide that we are not the supreme creators of the construct. Our constructs do not need to make that decision, only we do.",
        "SANDSWEPT_CANNONJELLY_NAME": "Ballistic Jellyfish",
        "SANDSWEPT_CANNONJELLY_LORE": "<style=cMono>\nWelcome to DataScraper (v3.1.53 - beta version)\n$ Scanning memory... done.\n$ Resolving... done.\n$ Fetching relevant data... done.\nReady!\n</style>\nUES report about incident: Incident 193442\nTwo employees reported seeing a Petrichoran jellyfish in the cabin of the rescue ship 'Safe Travels'. After 'liquidation', it was identified as a new species of Petrichoran, completely unrelated to the Petrichoran jellyfish.\nBeginning of transcription...\n\n«W-why is there a [REDActed] jellyfish in the [RemOVED] CABIN?»\n\n«I-I don't know! H-how would I know?»\n\n«You're the [REDacted] xenobiologist! I thought you had a book about all this?!»\n\n«L-look! She's in my room again... And also... Petrichoran jellyfish aren't normally... blue? This one... has a carapace.»\n\n[Sounds of fire crackling and the xenobiologist's scream of pain]\n\n«Shoot the damn thing, idiot! You're the bodyguard, since we're talking about roles!»\n\n[Sounds of m335 laser rifle shot and stone hitting the floor]\n\n«What kind of... thing is this? I- I don't even know what kingdom this creature belongs to, certainly neither animal nor macrobacteria...»\n\n«I don't know, you're the [REDacted] xenobiologist.»",
        "SANDSWEPT_SWEPSWEP_NAME": "Sweep-Sweep the Sandy",
        "ELITE_MOTIVATING_MODIFIER": "Motivating {0}",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_MOTIVATING_NAME": "John Hopoo",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_MOTIVATING_PICKUP": "Omg OwO <3 hii :3 x3 heyyy :3 :3 :3 UwU meow mrrraow OwO",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_MOTIVATING_DESCRIPTION": "Omg OwO <3 hii :3 x3 heyyy :3 :3 :3 UwU meow mrrraow OwO",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_MOTIVATING_LORE": "",
        "ELITE_OSMIUM_MODIFIER": "Osmium-Void {0}",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_OSMIUM_NAME": "Artificial Void",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_OSMIUM_PICKUP": "uzJ7tC6fFnk Be'come a/n a/spect o/f s/ing|ula/rity._ 3yd4myHf81E",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_OSMIUM_DESCRIPTION": "uzJ7tC6fFnk Be'come a/n a/spect o/f s/ing|ula/rity._ 3yd4myHf81E",
        "ELITE_EQUIPMENT_OSMIUM_LORE": "",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOID_SHRINE_RUIN_NAME": "Shrine of Ruin",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOID_SHRINE_RUIN_CONTEXT": "Offer to Shrine of Ruin",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOID_SHRINE_RUIN_USE_MESSAGE_2P": "<style=cShrine>Corruption spreads.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOID_SHRINE_RUIN_USE_MESSAGE": "<style=cShrine>Corruption spreads.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_OF_RUIN_DESCRIPTION": "When activated by a survivor, the Shrine of Ruin consumes 10 random white items from the inventory and corrupts the next stage.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_SACRIFICE_NAME": "Shrine of Sacrifice",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_SACRIFICE_CONTEXT": "Offer to Shrine of Sacrifice",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_SACRIFICE_USE_MESSAGE_2P": "<style=cShrine>Your time has been sacrificed.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_SACRIFICE_USE_MESSAGE": "<style=cShrine>{0}'s time has been sacrificed.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_SACRIFICE_DESCRIPTION": "When activated, the Shrine of Sacrifice consumes {curseCost}% of the survivor's maximum health in exchange for {itemCount} copies of a random common item.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_OF_SACRIFICE_DESCRIPTION": "When activated, the Shrine of Sacrifice consumes {curseCost}% of the survivor's maximum health in exchange for {itemCount} copies of a random common item.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_FUTURE_NAME": "Shrine of the Future",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_FUTURE_CONTEXT": "Offer to Shrine of the Future",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_FUTURE_USE_MESSAGE_2P": "<style=cShrine>Time has changed.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_FUTURE_USE_MESSAGE": "<style=cShrine>Time has distorted.</color>",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_OF_THE_FUTURE_DESCRIPTION": "When activated, the Shrine of the Future summons a random strong elite miniboss for each player that, when defeated, drops {itemCount} item potentials per player.",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_DEATH_NAME": "Shrine of Death",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_DEATH_CONTEXT": "Offer to Shrine of Death",
        "SANDSWEPT_SHRINE_DEATH_DESCRIPTION": "When activated, the Shrine of Death consumes {percentHealthCost}% of the survivor's health and disables all healing for {healingDisableDuration} seconds, but has {onKillProcChance}% chance to proc on-kill effects and {onInteractProcChance}% chance to proc on-interact effects.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_DRONE_BODY": "Voltaic Drone",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_DRONE_BROKEN_NAME": "Damaged Voltaic Drone",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_DRONE_CONTEXT": "Repair?",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_DRONE_BROKEN_DESCRIPTION": "A companion bought with gold that will follow the survivor at a short distance. Fires an electric bolt that electrocutes nearby targets.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_PRIM_NAME": "Jump Start",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_PRIME_DESC": "Fires an insertion rod that repeatedly electrocutes targets for 200% damage.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_OPERATOR_DESC": "Fires an insertion rod that repeatedly shocks targets for 600% damage, holding them in place.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_DESC": "Fires insertion rods that arc electricity to nearby targets for 200% damage.",
        "SANDSWEPT_VOLTAIC_PICKUP": "Fires insertion rods that electrocute targets.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_DRONE_BODY": "Inferno Drone",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_DRONE_BROKEN_NAME": "Damaged Inferno Drone",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_DRONE_CONTEXT": "Repair?",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_DRONE_BROKEN_DESCRIPTION": "A companion bought with gold that will follow the survivor at a short distance. Fires molotov cocktails.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_PRIM_NAME": "Scorch",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_PRIM_DESC": "Fires a rocket that leaves napalm pools for 3x300% damage per second.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_OPERATOR_DESC": "Advance and cover the ground, leaving napalm pools for 7x300% damage. Scales with attack speed.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_DESC": "Fires rockets at targets that create napalm pools for 300% damage per second.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INFERNO_PICKUP": "Fires rockets at targets that leave napalm pools.",
        "SANDSWEPT_OBJECTIVE_CHARGE_TP_EARLY": "Find and activate the <style=cDeath>Teleporter <sprite name=\"TP\" tint=1></style> in <style=cDeath>{0}s!</style>",
        "SANDSWEPT_OBJECTIVE_GET_UP_TO_X_ITEMS": "Get up to <style=cIsUtility>{0} items</style>.",
        "SANDSWEPT_INPUT_FEATHER": "Torn Feather Dash",
